Schools in England are maintained on the [Get information about schools](https://get-information-schools.service.gov.uk/)
(GIAS) service. We use this data to make it easier for the user to find a school.

When asking for a school

- give multiple methods of finding a school
- use [accessible autocomplete](https://github.com/alphagov/accessible-autocomplete)
to help a user when typing long school names
- use up to date data from Get information about schools
- display additional information to the user to help them identify the correct
school (such as the address)
- support those who do not have JavaScript enabled ([see School taught at non-JS fallback](../school-search-non-js-fallback))
- depending on what your service needs to do, distinguish between open and
closed schools
- do not use an autocomplete attribute

