#### If the input is empty

Say ‘Enter the name or postcode of the school’.

#### If no results match the search term

Say ‘No results match that search term. Try again.’

## Research on this pattern

Research on this pattern is limited. We've done some testing which indicates it
is usable and accessible, but we've also included an [option for users who are
unable to use JavaScript](../school-search-non-js-fallback).

### Employed to teach vs employed at

Most schools are part of a Multi Academy Trust (MAT) and teachers may not be employed by
the school they work at. For example, a teacher's employment contract could be
with the MAT, but they work at an academy within the MAT.

You can distinguish between asking where a teacher is employed and where they
work by using 'employed to teach at'.

### Open and closed schools

Some schools close then reopen with a new name, a slightly different name, or
the same name. In these cases GIAS will return more than one school. Only
display to the user the open school and discount the closed schools. If you need
to show a user closed schools:

- visually differentiate them to make it easier to pick
- display to the user when the school closed

