### Problems finding the right school

Some school names are more difficult to search for and identify.

Some schools are hard to distinguish between due to having similar names, for
example if there are multiple 'St Andrew's'.

A teacher may also type the school name differently to how it is spelt in the
GIAS data, for example typing 'Saint' instead of 'St' or using an apostrophe
differently.

For circumstances such as these, provide alternative methods of searching such
as by address or postcode as well as name.

You might also consider ignoring apostrophes and other punctuation in the
search.


